OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FVariable amounts of cloud and
OL,6,Fsome bright or sunny spells. There
OL,7,Fwill be a scattering of showers, these
OL,8,Fmost frequent across Argyll. Fewer
OL,9,Fshowers in the south.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FDry start this evening before
OL,12,Foutbreaks of rain spread from the
OL,13,Fsouthwest. Then cloudy overnight with
OL,14,Fspells of rain, turning persistent
OL,15,Facross the west later.
OL,16,
OL,17,CFriday:FRain spreading northeast for a
OL,18,Ftime in the morning. Then turning
OL,19,Fbrighter with a few showers,
OL,20,Foccasionally heavy later. Brisk
OL,21,Fsouthwesterly winds.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
